title: Sideline: CBC golfers receive A-A honors; CCS 7th football
text:
Sideline: CBC golfers receive A-A honors; CCS 7th football Posted: October 23, 2015 - 10:37pm CBC golfers receive A-A 
Two Central Baptist College golfers earned All-American status because of their efforts last week in the National Christian College Associationâ€™s national tournament at the Hombre Golf Club in Panama City, Fla. 
Austin Harmon of Bryant, who finished in a tie for fifth at 11-over 227 for three rounds, and Luke Cornett of Concord, who finished in a tie for 10th overall at 15-over 231, were honored for finishing in the top tier of golfers. 
The CBC men finished third overall. CCS 7th-graders down CSM 
Robert Taylor scored two touchdowns, a conversion and passed to Drew Strickland for another in a 36-18 victory Thursday night over Cutter Morning Star. 
Miguel Thorpe had an interception return for another score.
